BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-04-01-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board held an emergency meeting to address the COVID-19 pandemic and approved Resolution 22\, designating identified District public works projects as Essential Governmental Functions to continue operations under the San Mateo Public Health Order.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-04-01-board-meeting-2@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved multiple Bond Program projects across district schools\, including modernization work at Adelante Selby School\, architectural support at Clifford School\, and construction agreements at Taft School. The Board also adopted Resolution 21\, a resolution of emergency relating to COVID-19\, and discussed the district's response to the pandemic.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-04-15-special-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200415T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200415T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Special Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved construction agreements for Roosevelt School's Building E and the 2950 Fair Oaks Avenue site as part of the Measure T Bond Program\, adopted an updated bond budget\, and discussed paid leave provisions under the Families First Coronavirus Response Act.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-15/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-15/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-04-22-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200422T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200422T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved multiple bond program projects including change orders for modernization and construction work at Kennedy Middle School\, Adelante Selby\, and Hoover Community School\, as well as Resolution 24 for Energy Management System upgrades with Siemens. The Board also discussed revisions to student conduct and hate-motivated behavior policies (Board Policy 5131 and 5145.9)\, heard updates on COVID-19 impacts\, and approved the permanent renaming of the Selby Lane site as Adelante Selby Spanish Immersion School.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-22/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-22/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-05-06-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200506T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200506T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board held closed sessions to discuss property lease negotiations for 3150 Granger Way and labor negotiations with CSEA and RCTA\, while approving multiple Measure T Bond Program projects including fencing\, HVAC upgrades\, flooring\, and moving services across several schools. The Board also adopted Resolution 26 on classified services reductions for fiscal year 2020-21\, Resolution 27 approving tenured teachers\, and discussed new remote work and distance learning policies in response to COVID-19.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-05-06/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-05-06/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-05-20-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200520T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200520T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved multiple bond program projects including construction agreements for Roosevelt School and Orion Alternative School\, along with change orders for modernization work\, and adopted Resolution 28 on grading during emergency school closures. The Board also discussed school attendance boundary changes\, COVID-19 impacts\, and approved Board Policy 5141.52 on suicide prevention.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-05-20/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-05-20/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-06-03-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200603T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200603T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board discussed plans for the safe reopening of RCSD school campuses for the 2020-21 school year and approved updated contract language and tentative agreements with the RCTA.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-03/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-03/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-06-10-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200610T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200610T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board held public hearings on the 2020/21 Preliminary Budget\, COVID-19 operations\, and proposed school attendance boundary changes\, while also approving the permanent renaming of Selby Lane Elementary School to Adelante Selby Spanish Immersion School and multiple bond-funded facility projects including modernization work at Hoover Community School\, Kennedy Middle School\, Henry Ford Elementary School\, and Roosevelt School.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-10/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-10/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-06-17-special-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200617T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200617T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Special Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board held the first of two public hearings on school attendance boundary changes for neighborhood schools\, discussed the district's response to COVID-19 and school achievement plans\, adopted Resolution 32 calling for a November 3\, 2020 election for three Governing Board seats\, and approved permanently renaming Selby Lane Elementary School in Atherton as Adelante Selby Spanish Immersion School.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-17/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-17/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-06-24-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200624T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200624T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved the 2020-21 Proposed Budget for Redwood City School District and multiple Measure T Bond Program construction and modernization change orders across schools including McKinley Institute of Technology\, Adelante Selby Spanish Immersion School\, Taft Community School\, and Orion Alternative School. The Board also adopted Resolution 33 for preschool program funding\, approved new remote work policy 4113.5/4213.5/4313.5\, and discussed COVID-19 safety compliance and operations.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-24/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-06-24/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-07-15-special-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200715T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200715T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Special Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved multiple bond program construction and infrastructure projects across district schools\, including multi-prime agreements for Garfield School\, drainage upgrades at Adelante Selby Spanish Immersion School\, and IT wiring upgrades at Roosevelt School\, while also discussing the district's reopening plan and approving personnel changes and facility use agreements for the 2020-21 school year.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-07-15/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-07-15/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-07-22-special-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200722T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200722T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Special Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board held a closed session regarding existing litigation in Student v. Redwood City School District (OAH Case 2020060307)\, conducted a second public hearing on neighborhood schools attendance boundary changes\, and adopted the Roadmap to Reopening my School Plan for the 2020-21 school year. The Board also approved meal service agreements for Connect Community Charter School and KIPP Excelencia Community Prep Charter School\, and adopted updated Uniform Complaint Procedures to meet federal requirements.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-07-22/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-07-22/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-07-29-special-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200729T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200729T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Special Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved numerous bond program change orders and construction projects across multiple schools including Henry Ford Elementary\, Hoover Community School\, Taft Community School\, and Kennedy School\, along with adopting Board Policy 6157 on Distance Teaching and Learning and approving new attendance area boundaries for neighborhood schools.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-07-29/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-07-29/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-08-12-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200812T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200812T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved multiple Measure T Bond Program proposals for campus improvements including security systems at Adelante Selby School\, soil mitigation and testing projects at Orion Alternative School and Clifford School\, and classroom moving services at Roosevelt School\, while also adopting Resolution 3 and Resolution 4 regarding teaching assignments and classified services reductions for fiscal year 2020-21\, and approving updated RCTA contract language and tentative agreements.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-08-12/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-08-12/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-08-26-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200826T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200826T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved multiple Measure T Bond Program projects across district schools including gymnasium and modernization work at Hoover Community School\, new construction at Taft Community School\, and various facility improvements at Roosevelt and Orion Alternative School\, along with COVID-19 Safety Compliance Officer services and agreements with educational service providers for the 2020-21 school year.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-08-26/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-08-26/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-09-09-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200909T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200909T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The board approved a $200\,000 transfer from Program Contingency to Energy and Security Project and multiple facility improvement agreements for Orion Alternative School (formerly John Gill School) and Kennedy Middle School. The board also ratified agreements with community partners including Peninsula Community Center\, Sequoia Healthcare District\, and One Life Counseling to expand student support services\, and approved a new Memorandum of Understanding with the California School Employees Association.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-09/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-09/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-09-16-special-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200916T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200916T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Special Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board adopted the Measure T Bond Program budget study and update\, addressing the district's major capital improvement initiative. The meeting also included approval of previous board minutes and updates to the board agenda calendar.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-16/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-16/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-09-23-board-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200923T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200923T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board held a closed session regarding anticipated litigation\, approved multiple bond program items including $240\,000 in COVID-19 safety compliance funding and modernization projects at Kennedy Middle School and Roosevelt Elementary School\, and considered contract actions against Sausal Corporation for the Orion Alternative School modernization project. The Board also approved Board Policy 6157 on Distance Teaching and Learning and heard reports on the 6-8 Science Curriculum Pilot Process and COVID-19 impacts.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-23/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-23/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-09-30-special-meeting@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200930T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200930T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Special Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved the Learning Continuity and Attendance Plan for 2020-21 and the 2019-20 Unaudited Actuals Financial Statement\, and adopted Resolution 10 to establish the Gann Limit\, while also discussing the District's COVID-19 distance learning operations.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-30/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-09-30/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
